               <msContents>
                  <summary>The present text might acknowledge repayment of part of dowry. The writer is a woman by the name of Sarapia. Her own son, Apion, son of Melanion, grandson of Apion, is the recipient of this text; a husband is mentioned in l. 15.  The papyrus is, however, too mutilated to draw certain conclusions from or yield significant information.</summary>
